What makes an NFT project stand out to me?

1) Unique concepts with innovative ideas
2) Providing value to the community 
3) Transparency

(10/x) Here are some examples of problems with current NFT governance:
- Incentives of founder and community are not fully aligned
- Minimal checks and balances between the team and the community
- Minimal transparency, especially regarding use of funds

I believe the day is coming sooner than later where people are going to want a higher standard of verification for an NFT collection. You cannot have this much money, with this much technology and have no transparency into the people behind the projects.

content: NFTs are actually a great showcase for the emptiness of the promise of blockchain transparency. Pages aggregate prices and volume of NFT trades but because there is so much wash trading that data is public, accessible, not faked but also not the truth.

If a project's main way of gaining traction is a like, follow, retweet prize then walk away. Investors should demand honesty, transparency, informative updates, and detailed explanations of the project. If not you deserve to get rugged.

#BTC #ETH #Cardano #Solana #NFT #DeFi

8/It is clear to the community and me what went wrong: lack of transparency and empty promise after empty promise. I like transparency. I dislike empty promises. Let the past be nothing but a blemish on our journey together.

content:
NFT are more than a JPEG.

NFTs are:

‚Ä¢ Utility
‚Ä¢ Creativity
‚Ä¢ Access
‚Ä¢ Ownership
‚Ä¢ Efficiency 
‚Ä¢ Transparency 
‚Ä¢ Trust
‚Ä¢ Opportunity

NFTs are the future tech of all industries. Don‚Äôt put limits on what hasn‚Äôt been explored.

When I started my content creation journey I was presented with two options: 

Be fake, make more $$$ at the cost of others.

üß† their in real life (IRL) experience is relevant to the project

content:
People have asked me to address the ‚Äúenvironmental concerns of NFT‚Äù head on ‚Äî honestly I‚Äôve had a hard time knowing where to start

On the one hand we have technology that empowers creators and gives consumers critical protections and transparency in digital worlds #NFT

If only there was a way to add transparency to finance...

Is anybody even auditing these #NFT smart contracts? There‚Äôs a lot of fuckery going on. https://t.co/UOPPX4rNR3
Crypto adds transparency to the world of the actual rich, $60m for an NFT a decent bit minor taste of that

In the future we won‚Äôt no resume, employer will just need to look at your #NFT collection and will be able to see where you studied, work and even how good you were, full transparency, no more bullsh*t

NFT's are the talk of the digital art world these days, and while I love the idea of digital art as a collectible art-form that can bring fame and fortune to the people behind it, the lack of transparency about the ecological impact from the gallery sites is appalling..

more explicitly,

tired: NFT fever is an economic sham & ecological boondoggle; we know this only b/c of its similarity to trad art markets and transparency of POW blockchains

wired: venture-backed tech bullshit is a far larger, more pernicious economic & ecological catastrophe https://t.co/cdU9if1ZR8
Transparency what makes NFT the target, we don't know  how wasteful those movies, ads, games. Our entire life is a big waste. https://t.co/OgqS9nSKG0

Well it's not possible, so what do you do instead ? You criticize hard working creators trying to make ends meet. 
NFT brings transparency in the art world, it removes middlemen and gatekeepers.

Issuing NFT tickets in an easy way has its complexities. 

Let's look at how getNFTs deal with topics such as ticket transparency and upgradability. üëá
